title: PML-N’S Amir Talal Khan wins NA-178 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League (N) candidate, Amir Talal Khan has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-178, Muzaffargarh-IV by securing 113,816 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Independent candidate, Abdul Qayyom Khan Jatoi who bagged 87,932 votes.
The voters’ turn-out remained 52.35%.
